NUMBER 469
NAME Foyer
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
The entrance to the house is bright and airy. Directly in front of you are glass doors that open into a garden. Beyond the garden you can see a path that winds down to the sea. The walls and floors of this room are polished hardwood. To your right is an arch that leads into another larger room. To the left is a staircase that winds upwards. On a perch that looks out on the garden rests a vulture, who gazes at you with a hungry look in its beady eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END

